# Dev secret-store seed — Stream P (Mini-ADR P-13).
#
# The local_dev SecretStore (HELIX_AGENT_SECRET_STORE_ENV_FILE) reads this
# `name=value` file and resolves `secret://<name>` refs from agent manifests.
# This is how a dev injects a REAL LLM provider key so Phase 2/4/5 of the
# canonical-agent E2E can run a real turn (the platform does NOT ship a
# mock-LLM — Mini-ADR P-13).
#
#   1. cp infra/dev-keys/dev-llm-keys.example infra/dev-keys/dev-llm-keys.local
#   2. paste your real key into dev-llm-keys.local
#   3. docker compose --profile full up -d   (the compose mounts it +
#      sets HELIX_AGENT_SECRET_STORE_ENV_FILE, see infra/docker-compose.yml)
#
# dev-llm-keys.local is git-ignored (*.local). NEVER commit a real key.
#
# The name on the left MUST match the manifest's `api_key_ref` minus the
# `secret://` scheme. The canonical manifest references:
#     model.api_key_ref: secret://helix-agent/dev/llm/anthropic-api-key
helix-agent/dev/llm/anthropic-api-key=sk-ant-REPLACE-WITH-YOUR-KEY

# Tavily key backing the built-in web_search tool (optional — web_search
# returns an error without it, the rest of the agent still runs).
# helix-agent/dev/tools/tavily-api-key=tvly-REPLACE-WITH-YOUR-KEY
